<figureCitation id="13512A00FFC0FFD6FCDCFE53BCF9CEDE" box="[893,972,446,472]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="18.[136,229,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,794,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-56@18.[183,1404,794,1912]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 11. Puccinia circaeae-caricis on Circaea sp. (A–H) and Carex sp. (I). A. Plants producing spermogonia and aecia on the leaf surface in the field. B, D. Aecia on the lower leaf surface. C. Vertical section of a spermogonium. E. Vertical section of an aecium surrounded with peridia. F. Aeciospores. G. An aecium observed under SEM. H. Aeciospores with granules on the surface observed under SEM. I. Vertical section of a telium. Scale bars: C, F, I = 20 μm, E, G = 50 μm, H = 5 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6416785" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6416785/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
