<subSubSection id="C370650EFFC0FFD6FF29FDEBBE05CC46" pageId="19" pageNumber="240" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFC0FFD6FF29FDEBBE05CC46" blockId="19.[136,1452,518,1444]" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FF29FDEBBE29CD26" bold="true" box="[136,284,518,544]" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Description:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FE99FDEABEF8CD27" box="[312,461,519,545]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Spermogonia</emphasis>
amphigenous, surrounded by greenish yellow lesions, densely grouped, honey-yellow, subepidermal, flask-shaped, 
<typeStatus id="54D18827FFC0FFD6FE6FFDC6BECBCD43" box="[462,510,555,581]" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">type</typeStatus>
4 of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFC0FFD6FDE3FDC7BCA8CD42" author="Cummins, G. B. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y." box="[578,925,554,580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="240" refId="ref19116" refString="Cummins, G. B. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y. (2003) Illustrated genera of rust fungi, 3 rd ed. American Phytopathological Society, St. Paul, Minnesota, USA." type="book" year="2003">Cummins &amp; Hiratsuka (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FC0AFDC6BCDECD43" box="[939,1003,555,581]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Aecia</emphasis>
is mostly hypophyllous, cupulate with peridia, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFC0FFD6FF47FDA3BE65CD6E" box="[230,336,590,616]" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Aecidium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="19" pageNumber="240" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FF47FDA3BE65CD6E" box="[230,336,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Aecidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus id="54D18827FFC0FFD6FEF9FDA2BEB8CD6F" box="[344,397,591,617]" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">type</typeStatus>
. Peridial cells firmly conjunct, cubic to polygonal, hyaline. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FBE0FDA2BBFCCD6F" box="[1089,1225,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Aeciospores</emphasis>
catenulate, globose to subglobose, angular, 10.5–14.5 × 9.5–12.5 µm (av. 12.5 × 11.0 µm); walls hyaline, 0.3–0.6 µm (av. = 0.4 µm) thick, densely verrucose with big granules. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FDDFFD7BBDD7CDB6" box="[638,738,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Uredinia</emphasis>
rarely found. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FC29FD7BBC8ACDB6" box="[904,959,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Telia</emphasis>
hypophyllous, blackish brown, rounded to broadly elliptic, erumpent. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFC0FFD6FE17FD57BD00CDD2" box="[438,565,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="240">Teliospores</emphasis>
broadly clavate, ellipsoid, rounded or conical at apices, constricted at the septa, attenuate at the bases, 29.5–41.0 × 13.0–19.0 µm (av. 35.5 × 15.5 µm); walls pale brown, 0.6–0.9 µm (av. 0.8 µm) thick at sides, darker at the apex 4.0–11.8 µm (av. 7.2 µm) at apices; pedicels persistent, hyaline, 10.5–25.0 µm (av. 17.0 µm) long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
